<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Opens U.S. Trip in Los Angeles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
arrived here this morning on special plane, opening his eight-day
official visit to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Guest of President Bill Clinton, Zhu is the first Chinese
premier to visit the United States in 15 years. It is believed
that during his visit, Zhu will have an extensive and in-depth
exchange of views with American leaders on Sino-U.S. relations as
well as major international and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
The special plane arrived in the International Airport at 8:45.
Los Angeles Mayor Richard Riordan, and Li Zhaoxing, one of Zhu's
entourage and Chinese ambassador to the United States, went aboard
to escort the premier and his wife Lao An.
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles gave the Chinese premier a red-carpet welcome.
Carrying the national flags of China and the United States, two
guards stood beside the ramp. Two American children presented
flowers to the premier and his wife.
</P>
<P>
Present at the airport to welcome Zhu and his wife were U.S.
ambassador to China James Sasser and Mrs. Sasser, Mrs. Riordan,
Deputy Assistant to the Secretary of State Susan Shirk, and Vice
Chairperson of the Board of Directors of the National Committee on
United States-China Relations Mrs. Howard Ahmanson.
</P>
<P>
Also present were Chinese Consul General to Los Angeles An
Wenbin, as well as more than 300 representatives of the local
Chinese community and Chinese students studying in California.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement issued at the airport, Premier Zhu said
that his visit is to build on the successful exchange of visits by
President Jiang Zemin and President Clinton, implement the
agreement they have reached, deepen mutual understanding, expand
mutually beneficial cooperation and push forward China-U.S.
relations further in the direction of a constructive strategic
partnership.
</P>
<P>
The premier's entourage included State Councilor Wu Yi, State
Councilor and Secretary-General of the State Council Wang Zhongyu,
Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, Minister in charge of the State
Development Planning Commission Zeng Peiyan, and Minister of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Shi Guangsheng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
