<HEADLINE> U.N. Preparing for Millennium Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations is
organizing regional hearings in preparation for the 55th session
of U.N. General Assembly in September next year, which deals with
U.N. mission in the next century, U.N. said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of governments and civil society will gather
over the next five months to debate how the world body can best
achieve its goals, U.N. Department of Public Information said.
</P>
<P>
They will discuss central aspects of the work of the U.N. such
as its efforts in the areas of economic and social affairs,
development cooperation and humanitarian relief.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East, Africa, Europe, the Asia-Pacific and the Latin
America-Caribbean are the regions which will hold the hearings,
DPI said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The hearings will be started from May 23-24 in Beirut at the
Economic and Social Commission for Western Asia, and will end with
the meeting of the Economic Commission for Latin America and the
Caribbean in September.
</P>
<P>
Based on the outcome of these hearings, U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan is expected to produce a report to U.N. member states
of the United Nations in the new century, DPI added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
