<HEADLINE> Arab Human Rights Group Deplores Israeli Inhumane </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 6 (Xinhua) -- An Arab human rights group Tuesday
strongly deplored the inhumane practices by the Israeli authorities
against Arab people.
</P>
<P>
The Arab Organization for Human Rights said in a periodical
newsletter circulated here Tuesday that it had received
information about the deteriorating conditions of Lebanese
prisoners in Israel's Khayam prison, with many of them suffering
from serious illness.
</P>
<P>
The organization said that it has the names of 24 prisoners who
are in a serious condition. Some of them are under the age of 18,
it added.
</P>
<P>
The organization called on the international community to
pressure the Israeli government to stop torturing the Arabs while
urging the international public opinion to make efforts to seek
the release of the Lebanese prisoners.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from Lebanese
guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
The Jewish state has jailed many Lebanese who fought against
its occupation in south Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
