<HEADLINE> Former Burundi Hutu President Remembered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 6 (Xinhua) -- A mass commemorating the death of
the late Burundi president, Cyprien Ntaryamira, was held in the
Burundi capital Bujumbura Tuesday, official sources announced.
</P>
<P>
Ntaryamira was killed in a plane crash over Rwandan capital
Kigali on April 6, 1994 along with Rwandan Hutu president Juvenal
Habyarimana. The death of the two presidents was followed by
ethnic violence which spiraled into genocide in Rwanda, claiming
the lives of over 500,000 Tutsis and Hutu moderates.
</P>
<P>
"The mass was attended by the Burundi President Major Pierre
Buyoya, the two vice-presidents, and several other political,
military and religious leaders," Rwanda News Agency reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Evariste Ngoyagoye, the Bishop Bujumbura, who led prayers
praised the Burundi people who are striving for peace, but noted
that there is a long way to go as some politicians continue to
wrangle for power.
</P>
<P>
The ceremonies ended with the laying of a wreath of flowers on
Nyaryamira's grave and that of two ministers killed in the same
crash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
