neighboring Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia (FYROM) to cope
with the wave of refugees from Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, Reppas said that Greece was fully
prepared to do so. He added that Greek Prime Minister Costas
Simitis had spoken with his FYROM counterpart Ljubco Georgievski
