over the former's name was "a separate issue" that was being dealt
with in the framework of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that the Kosovo crisis might create better
understanding leading to a resolution of the name issue.
</P>
<P>
Greece has agreed to take in some 5,000 refugees from Kosovo
following a weekend announcement by Skopje that it could receive
no more refugees without guarantees and that the refugees would be
redirected to another country.
</P>
<P>
To deal with the refugee problem, Greece has decided to
establish refugee centers around the country and to give 2.5
billion U.S. dollars in aid to Albania, FYROM and Serbia. 
