<HEADLINE> Strange Disease Kills 4 Kids in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- A strange disease had killed four
children in Angolan capital Luanda in four days up to last Friday,
according to a report released by the Angolan National Bureau of
Public Health.
</P>
<P>
The report available here Tuesday said that 102 cases were
reported in the capital and the the excrement samples of the sick
children have been sent to South Africa for stool examination so
as to find out the cause of the strange disease and its cure.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that children under the age of six years are
easy to be affected by the disease which causes muscle paralysis.
</P>
<P>
The four kids died from chest muscle paralysis, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan health authorities for the time being called such
disease "acute flaccid paralysis" and suspected that it was caused
by contaminated food and water.
</P>
<P>
Since late March, the hospitals in Luanda has received a lot of
sick children from the areas surrounding the capital city. The
kids seemed to have caught influenza. But several days after the
fever was gone, they could no longer stand or walk.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan health authorities have specially established a
medical committee to study the disease and its cure and asked all
the hospitals across the country to keep close watch at the
disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
