<HEADLINE> 42 Zimbabweans Killed During Easter Road Accidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 6 (Xinhua) -- A total of 42 Zimbabweans were
killed and 381 others injured in road accidents during the Easter
holidays, police said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Police Deputy Commissioner George Kundeya told a press
conference that the worst accident during the Easter holidays from
last Friday to Monday, occurred in Nyazura of east Zimbabwe where
a bus overturned, killing 11 people.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 31 people were killed while 352 others were injured
during the same period.
</P>
<P>
Kundeya said most of the accidents were caused by drunken
driving, vehicle defects and speeding.
</P>
<P>
The police officer said that three people were arrested for
drunken driving Monday alone while 21 vehicles were impounded and
1,825 tickets were issued for traffic offenses.
</P>
<P>
"These figures are not acceptable and more stern measures will
continue to be implemented to reduce the carnage on our roads," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"Police will continue to mount 24-hour road checks," he said,
adding that the accidents had shown motorists did not take heed of
police warnings which compelled every driver to exercise
responsibility on the road. 
</P>
</TEXT>
