<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-06 20:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Turkey to Further Develop Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- China and Turkey on Tuesday agreed
to further develop bilateral ties in all fields.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached during talks between Turkish
President Suleyman Demirel and visiting Chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress of China Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
Demirel said that Turkey attaches great importance to
developing friendly ties with China, which is playing an important
role in the world.
</P>
<P>
Terming the development of bilateral ties as smooth, the
Turkish president said there had been no obstacles or problems
whatsoever between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the principle of non-interference in other countries'
internal affairs, the Turkish government is opposed to any
anti-China separatist activities and other terrorist activities
targeting China, Demirel said.
</P>
<P>
Turkey was fully aware that this was a sensitive issue to the
feelings of the Chinese people and promised to handle the issue
properly, said the president.
</P>
<P>
Demirel also pointed out that what a small number of
anti-China separatists did never represented the policies of the
Turkish government.
</P>
<P>
Turkey highly appreciates the correct policies of the Chinese
government on minority ethnic groups, particularly those on
helping the Xinjiang Uigur Autonomous Region develop its economy
and raise the living standards of the people there, the president
said.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the two countries will further promote
cooperation in such areas as trade and economy, culture and
tourism.
</P>
<P>
Echoing Demirel's evaluation on bilateral ties, the top Chinese
legislator said there was no fundamental conflict of interests
between China and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
"What we have are merely friendship, understanding and
cooperation," Li said, adding that China highly appreciates the
correct stance of the Turkish government on the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
"President Demirel once again made it clear that the Turkish
government is opposed to all forms of anti-China separatist
activities and violent terrorist activities in Turkey," Li said,
this "fully demonstrated the wise policy of the Turkish
leadership."
</P>
<P>
China believes that the mutual understanding and trust on
matters of major principle importance forms the basis on which
China and Turkey can develop their all-around cooperative
relations.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived in Turkey Friday on a five-day official visit as
part of a six-nation Euro-Asian tour. Li had visited Greece and
will continue the trip to Syria, Pakistan, Bangladesh and
Thailand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
