<HEADLINE> Egypt to Send Relief to Kosovars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Egypt has decided to send relief to
Kosovo ethnic Albanian refugees, sources of the Egyptian Red
Crescent Society said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the humanitarian aid will be flown Wednesday
to the refugees, who have been pouring into neighboring Albania
and Macedonia since the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO)
began its air-strikes against Serb targets on March 24.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the relief goods include 5.4 tonnes of
medicines, 1,500 boxes of milk powder, 500 boxes of canned
foodstuffs and 1,000 blankets, the Middle East News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Tensions between Serb-led Yugoslav government and the ethnic
Albanians in the province of Kosovo intensified early last year
after the Albanians sought independence from Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
NATO began bombing Serb targets after Yugoslav President
Slobodan Milosevic refused to sign a peace agreement, which
requires Belgrade to grant autonomy to the ethnic Albanians in
Kosovo and allow NATO to deploy peace-keeping forces in the
province. 
