program to purchase oil spare parts, an Iraqi Oil Ministry
official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Director General of the Planning and Studies Department at the
Oil Ministry Falih Hassan Marhoon told the Iraqi News Agency that
39 contracts worth 24 million dollars had been submitted to the
U.N. Sanctions Committee for ratification. (BC-Iraq-Contracts)
</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress of China, arrived here Tuesday on a
three-day official visit to Syria.
</P>
<P>
Abdel Kader Kaddura, Speaker of the People's Council of Syria
(parliament) accorded Li a warm welcome at the Damascus
International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters at the airport shortly after brief talks
with Kaddura, Li said he was expecting in-depth talks with Syrian
leaders on bilateral and international issues of common interest.
(BC-Syria-China)
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Palestinian offices in East Jerusalem shut
down by Israel will appeal the closure orders to Israel's High
Court of Justice, the Voice of Palestine reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Jawad Bulus, the lawyer appointed by the three Palestinian
offices, said the closure orders issued by Israeli government were
"political, not legal," the radio said. (BC-Israel-Closure)
</P>
