<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Reserve Assets Drops 272 Million Dollars Last week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- U.S. official reserve assets
dropped 272 million dollars last week to 73.98 billion dollars,
the Treasury Department said.
</P>
<P>
The Department said that the decrease compared with a revised
746 million dollars decline the previous week.
</P>
<P>
U.S. reserve assets consist of foreign currencies, gold,
special drawing rights at the International Monetary Fund and the
U.S. reserve position at the IMF.
</P>
<P>
The nation's holdings of foreign currencies increased 25
million dollars last week to 30.08 billion dollars, while its gold
reserves were unchanged at 11.05 billion dollars. Holdings of IMF
special drawing rights dropped 87 million to 9.67 billion dollars,
and the nation's reserve position at the IMF fell 209 million to
23.19 billion dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
