<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece's Inflation Drops to 3.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Greece's inflation dropped from 3.7
percent in February to 3.4 percent in March of this year, Greece's
National Statistics Service (NSS) announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Annual inflation stood at 4.6 percent and 6.0 percent in March
in 1998 and 1997 respectively.
</P>
<P>
The NSS expected the country's inflation to drop significantly
in April.
</P>
<P>
Greece, which wants to join the euro zone in 2001 and satisfy
the convergence criteria this year, aims to contain inflation to
2.0 percent by the end of the first half of 1999. 
</P>
