<HEADLINE> Albanian Parliament Approves NATO Deployment of Apache Helicopters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian parliament on
Wednesday passed a law allowing NATO to deploy 24 Apache
Helicopters in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government on Tuesday approved the draft law at an
urgent session and submitted it to the parliament for approval in
response to a NATO demand for deploying the heavily armed
helicopters in Albania as soon as possible. The law has taken
immediate effect.
</P>
<P>
After two weeks of bombing by high-flying jets, which failed to
get significant fruits, NATO decided to introduce Apache
helicopter gunships to the campaign of airstrikes on Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Apaches, flown with a crew of two, are armed with 16 Hellfire
missiles designed to knock out tanks and armored vehicles. The
press here said such a move was aimed at making preparations for
possible invasion of NATO ground troops into Yugoslavia. 
</P>
