<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Foreign Currency Assets Lower in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The official foreign currency
assets of Hong Kong amounted to 89.5 billion U.S. dollars at the
end of March, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
This is 0.3 billion U.S. dollars less than the 89.8 billion U.S.
dollars at the end of February.
</P>
<P>
The small decrease in foreign currency assets can mainly be
attributed to reversal in the note issuing activities in March
after the Chinese New Year holidays in February this year, said
the HKMA.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong remains the world's fourth largest holder of foreign
currency reserves after Japan (222.5 billion U.S. dollars at the
end of March), the Chinese mainland (146.0 billion U.S. dollars at
the end of February) and Taiwan (93.0 billion U.S. dollars at the
end of March).
</P>
<P>
The total foreign currency assets of 89.5 billion U.S. dollars
represent over seven times the currency circulation or about 40
percent of Hong Kong dollar M3, one of the highest ratios in the
world, the HKMA said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
