<HEADLINE> Rockets And Hunters lead Series 2-0 in CBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Three-time defending champion Bayi
Rockets held off a strong fourth-quarter rally from the Beijing
Aoshen to score a 108-104 thrilling victory on Wednesday, holding
a 2-0 lead in the best of five semifinals series.
</P>
<P>
22-year-old Wang Zhizhi scored 30 points to lead four Bayi
players finished in double figures. The 7-foot center also grabbed
11 rebounds and blocked 5 Aoshen shots.
</P>
<P>
Bayi led the first half by 54-49.
</P>
<P>
Aoshen played a tough defense and took over the lead by 86-85
with just three minutes into the fourth quarter. But that was the
first and last time Aoshen went ahead and the sharp shooting
Rockets soon regained the edge and never looked back through the
rest of the game.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets outrebounded Aoshen 43-34.
</P>
<P>
In the other semifinal game on Wednesday, Liaoning Hunters used
fastbreaking to beat the Guangdong Tigers 126-94.
</P>
<P>
Guard Guo Liqiang hit a game high 33 points to led the Hunters,
who also took a 2-0 led in the best of five series.
</P>
<P>
In the elimination round to decide the bottom two teams drop to
the second division, Zhang Cheng scored 40 points, his third 40 or
more play of the season, to led Jiangsu Dragon to a 120-111
victory over Sichuan Pandas while Jilin Northeast Tigers trounced
Jinan Army Pegasus 112-92. 
</P>
</TEXT>
