<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Unveils Small Industries Development Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Wednesday unveiled
the Small and Medium Industries (SMIs) Development Plan in an
initiative to create a more conducive business environment for the
manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
The plan under the auspices of the Small and Medium Industries
Development Corporation (SMIDEC) would enable SMIs to face new
challenges brought about by the changing business environment,
especially under the current economic situation, International
Trade and Industry Minister Rafidah Aziz said.
</P>
<P>
The plan will evaluate the strengths and weaknesses of domestic
SMIs involved in manufacturing and related services in terms of
technology, technical skills or human resource development, market
access and finance, she said.
</P>
<P>
The plan would also access the capability and competitiveness
of the domestic SMIs in supplying critical parts and components to
large industries in selected industry clusters, she said.
</P>
<P>
"It (the plan) will also look into further developing and
strengthening potential linkages within selected industrial
linkages," she was quoted by the Malaysian national news agency
Bernama as saying at the 1999 Annual MITI (Ministry of
International Trade and Industry) Dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, the SMI Technology Capability Roadmap will be
developed to enhance the technological capabilities of
manufacturers in the production process and product development.
</P>
</TEXT>
