<HEADLINE> India, Qatar Sign Cooperation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- India and Qatar Wednesday signed
three cooperation documents in a bid to enhance their bilateral
economic relations.
</P>
<P>
The documents included an agreement on the avoidance of double
taxation to boost investments and another on bilateral investment
protection and promotion, and a memorandum of understanding for
enhancing bilateral cooperation in the private sector.
</P>
<P>
The documents were agreed upon during the visit of Qatar Emir
Hamad bin Khalifa al-Thani, who arrived here Tuesday on a
three-day state visit.
</P>
<P>
The emir was earlier accorded a red carpet welcome at the
Presidential Palace by Indian President Kocheril Raman Narayanan
and Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee.
</P>
<P>
This was the emir's first visit to India at the head of a
high-level delegation including the deputy prime minister.
</P>
<P>
During the emir's stay here, the leaders of the two countries
will hold wide-ranging discussions on international, regional and
bilateral issues of mutual concern, official sources said.
</P>
