<HEADLINE> Highway Key to Macao's Handover Opened to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A highway, which is vital to the
ceremonies in connection with the handover of Macao from Portugal
to China at the end of this year, was opened to traffic this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Consisting of two overpasses and a section of coastal road, the
highway strings together the Macao Cultural Center for Portuguese
officials to hold a farewell gathering, a site for the handover
ceremony and the Macao Forum for the ceremony marking the
establishment of the future Macao Special Administrative Region (
SAR).
</P>
<P>
All the three sites are not far from the Ferry Terminal linking
up Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the highway took nearly one year with an
investment of 43 million patacas (5.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
