<DOCNO> XIE19990407.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Patches Loopholes in Investment Supervision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Finance has asked
local authorities to strengthen fund management and the
supervision of infrastructure construction projects in order to
stamp out waste and the diversion of treasury money.
</P>
<P>
In a circular released today, the Ministry of Finance pointed
out that there are "non-ignorable problems" in these areas.
</P>
<P>
China increased investment in infrastructure facilities by 100
billion yuan by issuing additional treasury bonds in the latter
half of last year, inflating the budget deficit to over 150
billion yuan this year from less than 100 billion yuan last year
in order to stimulate economic growth.
</P>
<P>
However, the ministry noted that spending on many construction
projects greatly exceeds their budget due to inadequate pre-
project study, that other projects fail to conclude on schedule
due to lack of supplementary funds, and that funds for still other
projects are diverted or wasted because of poor financial
management.
</P>
<P>
"If these problems are not resolved and corrected immediately,
they will severely affect the efficiency of investment in
infrastructure construction, damage the results of the pro-active
financial policy, and produce great losses and waste of funds,"
the circular said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance asks leaders of local governments to
take direct responsibility for ensuring efficient fund use in
these projects.
</P>
<P>
It requires that local authorities not provide treasury funds
for projects that lack supplementary funds. It also states that
the central government will reduce funding for local construction
projects if local governments fail to provide adequate
supplementary funds.
</P>
<P>
It further requires that relevant authorities stamp out the
diversion and waste of treasury funds.
</P>
<P>
The circular warns that persons responsible for waste and
diversion of treasury funds and other severe violations will be
punished and may even face criminal charges.
</P>
<P>
Since most of the money the central government assigns for
infrastructure construction projects is raised through the
issuance of treasury bonds, the Ministry of Finance also requires
local governments to make practical plans to guarantee repayment.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji pointed out earlier this year that using
bond money to fund these construction projects will enhance
economic growth and increase the growth potential of the economy.
</P>
<P>
He also asked that the money be used for careful planning and
the guaranteeing of engineering quality, while fund diversion and
the waste of treasury funds be eliminated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990407.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
