<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inter-clan Fighting Kills 11 in C. Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 7 (Xinhua) -- At least 11 people were killed
and more than 15 others were wounded in an inter-clan fighting
between the Badi Addeh and Jareer communities in Somalia's central
Hiran region Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses who fled the fighting told Xinhua Wednesday that
nearly 200 men from both sides and armed with assault rifles,
rocket propelled grenades and hand bombs were involved in the
clashes outside the second largest district of Bulo Burto, 240
kilometers north of Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The opposing militiamen launched attack and counter-attack
operations on three villages inhabited by the two clansmen, they
said.
</P>
<P>
Independent sources said that the three villages of Dabayodleh,
 Samatarow and Aqab were erased and burnt down to ashes as each
side had staged successive attacks on those villages in their
attempt of clearing the area from the opponent clansmen.
</P>
<P>
Two of the burnt villages belonged to the Badi Addeh clansmen
while the third belonged to the Jareer men.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the fighting between the two sides is said to
have related to a dispute over the contract in repairing a water
well in the village of Dabayodleh.
</P>
<P>
Two week ago, six men from the Badi Addeh clan were killed by
the Jareer clansmen in relation to the contract dispute.
</P>
<P>
A local aid agency, ADRA, has been digging and repairing water
wells for the local communities in the region where water
scarcity has been claiming both human and livestock lives during
the prolonged drought in the region.
</P>
<P>
Efforts were made by the traditional leaders to contain the
hostility which is draining up the resources of the region since
it coincided with the time of the cultivation even though the
rains did not fall as expected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
