<HEADLINE> Chinese, Mexican Defense Ministers Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian met here today with his Mexican counterpart Enrique
Cervantes Aguirre.
</P>
<P>
Chi happily reviewed his trip to Mexico last month, and
expressed his thanks again to Cervantes for the hospitality he was
accorded by Cervantes and the Mexican army.
</P>
<P>
Though of different social systems, Chi said, China and Mexico
share many common views and interests, and therefore should
support each other to further promote friendship and cooperation
at all levels and in all fields between the two nations and the
two armies.
</P>
<P>
On the international situation, Chi, who is also vice chairman
of the Central Military Commission and a state councilor, said
that the Chinese government strongly urges NATO to immediately
stop air strikes against Yugoslavia. The international community
and relevant parties in Yugoslavia concerned should work together
to ease the situation and restore peace in the region as soon as
possible, he added.
</P>
<P>
Cervantes voiced the hope that his visit will lend impetus to
the development of bilateral army relations.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican government stands by China in opposing hegemonism
and power politics, he said, adding that Mexico insists on solving
the Kosovo crisis through political means.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, Chi held a welcoming ceremony for the
Mexican guests who will also visit several military barracks here.
They also are scheduled to visit Xi'an, Hangzhou, and Shanghai.
</P>
