<HEADLINE> China to Host International Seminar on Educational Use of Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- An international seminar on
educational opportunities and the Internet will be held here April
22-24, the Chinese Education Association for International
Exchange (CEAIE) said today.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 educators, scientists and entrepreneurs from
China, the United States, Sweden and the Netherlands will attend
the three-day event, which is jointly sponsored by the CEAIE and
the International Business University of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Co-sponsors of the event also includes a California-based
technological university.
</P>
<P>
During the seminar, discussions will be held on many hot
educational topics including education via the Internet, China's
education in 21st century, the present and future role of long-
distance education in China and the United States, American
education and international cooperation, and education
modernization and opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Shen Xuesong, a CEAIE official, said the seminar's theme is the
further development of China's Internet-education capabilities and
exchanges with foreign countries in the fields of information
technology and use of educational resources.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, educators from the United States will
demonstrate a series of Internet equipment for long-distance
education and the technological development of teaching materials.
</P>
