<HEADLINE> Contact Group Officials Meet on Kosovo in Brussels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The six-nation Contact Group on
the former Yugoslavia met here Wednesday at the level of political
directors of foreign ministries, trying to reconsider how the big
powers would deal with the complicated situation in the Balkan
region after two-week NATO air attacks on Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Contact Group meeting was held at the German Embassy in
Belgium for the first time since the Rambouillet talks broke off
and NATO started to bomb Yugoslavia, a sovereign nation in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The Contact Group, comprising the United States, Russia,
Germany, France, Britain and Italy, is expected to look for ways
to settle the complicated crisis currently not only in Kosovo but
in the whole region, diplomatic sources said.
</P>
<P>
Russia, the Itar Tass news agency said, is represented by Boris
Mayorsky, who was one of international mediators at the talks
between the Yugoslav and Kosovo Albanian delegations in
Rambouillet, France.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, European Union (EU) interior ministers are holding a
special meeting in Luxembourg to discuss the possibility of
providing aid to Kosovo refugees and arranging provisional
accommodation for tens of thousands of refugees in some EU
countries.
</P>
<P>
An emergency meeting of EU foreign ministers is also to be held
in Luxembourg on Thursday to discuss the Kosovo crisis and to
assess the new situation following the two weeks of NATO bombing
strikes against Yugoslavia. 
</P>
