<HEADLINE> Shanghai Joins Master Card International Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,100 automatic teller
machines (ATM) and over 8,700 point of sale (POS) machines in
Shanghai, China's financial hub, were connected to the Master Card
International network today.
</P>
<P>
This move will enable hundreds of millions of Master Card
holders worldwide to use ATMs in Shanghai, said Master Card
International.
</P>
<P>
Now, Shanghai has joined the networks of both Master Card
International and Visa International, the two major international
payment systems.
</P>
<P>
The municipal Bankcard Network, made up of 13 major Chinese
financial institutions, is already connected with the National
Bankcard Processing Center as well as the Shanghai branches of
Citibank and the Hong Kong and Shanghai Banking Corporation,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Master Card International entered the Chinese market in 1987,
and has issued over 27 million Master Cards in China. 
</P>
