<HEADLINE> Samsung Develops 3-D TFT-LCD Monitor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 7 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's Samsung Electronics
Company Wednesday said it has developed a three-dimensional (3-D)
thin film transistor-liquid crystal display (TFT-LCD) monitor.
</P>
<P>
The 17-inch flat-screen monitor, which creates a 3-D image by
inserting a glass between the two LCD circuits, is suitable for a
variety of simulated situations that require virtual reality.
</P>
<P>
With a price tag of about 10 million won (some 86,000 U.S.
dollars the product will be particularly useful for multimedia
games and remote-controlled tasks, including deep-sea operations,
Samsung said.
</P>
<P>
Samsung plans to sell 1,000 3-D flat-screen monitors in the
domestic market and export 10,000 units this year.
</P>
<P>
The company said it will develop a 21-inch TFT-LCD monitor in
the second half of this year and 30-inch product next year.
</P>
</TEXT>
