<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Receive Gas from Pinghu Oil Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Oil and Natural Gas
Corporation announced today that the municipality will receive
natural gas supplies from the Pinghu Oil Field in the East China
Sea beginning tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
A daily supply of 300,000 cubic meters of natural gas will be
offered by the oil field to Shanghai in the short term, and the
scale will be upgraded to 1.2 million cubic meters by the end of
this year, the company said.
</P>
<P>
However, the natural gas will not be available to Shanghai
citizens until the end of this month as the gas company in
Shanghai still has some preparatory work to do, said local
officials.
</P>
<P>
The 240-square-kilometer oil field, the first of its kind ever
found in the East China Sea, has total gas reserves of 10.8
billion cubic meters. About 20 square kilometers of the oil field
has undergone first-stage exploration.
</P>
<P>
The wide use of natural gas will promote the adjustment of
Shanghai's energy structure, which will be conducive to the
improvement of the air quality in the city, experts said.
</P>
</TEXT>
