</P>
<P>
-- Scottish police formally charged two former Libyan
intelligence agents with the bombing of Pan Am flight 103 over
Scotland in 1988 in a short session for which the United States
and Britain had waited for more than a decade.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- The WTO backed U.S. claims that the European Union's banana-
import policies violate international rules, a significant
American victory in an escalating series of trade disputes.
</P>
<P>
-- A top treasury official warned Europe against relying on
exports to offset weakening economies and said Western Europe's
policies are partly to blame for its economic problems. 
</P>
