<HEADLINE> Egyptian President Visits Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Muhammed Hosni
Mubarak today visited Tianjin, a major industrial and city 120
kilometers east of Beijing, where he met with Mayor Li Shenglin.
</P>
<P>
Li said Tianjin has had a good cooperative relationship with
Egypt, and construction of the special economic zone in the Gulf
of Suez has been advancing with the help of the Tianjin Economic
Development Area (TEDA).
</P>
<P>
He noted that a Tianjin business delegation had reached an
agreement with Egypt on eleven projects during their recent visit
to Cairo.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the visit of President Mubarak will promote
economic cooperation between Tianjin and Egypt.
</P>
