Egypt and Tianjin, and see the agreement through to implementation.
</P>
<P>
He said the Egyptian government is ready to help solve problems
occurring in bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The president and his party then visited the TEDA and the
Motorola corporation.
</P>
<P>
China's first overseas economic zone, the special economic zone
in the Gulf of Suez, was undertaken by the TEDA.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Egypt has invested in three Tianjin
businesses, involving two million U.S. dollars, and trade volume
between Tianjin and Egypt climbed to 28 million dollars in 1998.
</P>
