<HEADLINE> Fed Cup Format Changed for 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Fed Cup women's team tennis
event will undergo several changes next year, with 13 teams
instead of eight qualifying for the World Group, the International
Tennis Federation announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 1999 champions will have a bye through to the finals next
year while the other 12 teams battle through three round robin
groups in three venues over one calendar week.
</P>
<P>
Under the new format the eight teams from the 1999 World Group
One will be joined by four winning teams from the first round of
World Group Two and a 13th team emerging from a play-off. 
</P>
</TEXT>
