<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Qian Meets Hong Kong Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Qian Qichen here
today met a delegation from the Hong Kong Overseas Chinese General
Association led by Ku Suen Fai.
</P>
<P>
Qian told them that their association has played an important
role in guaranteeing the smooth return of Hong Kong to the
motherland and maintaining the region's prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
He said that the central government has always attached
importance to the role of overseas Chinese, who are patriotic and
have deep feelings for the motherland. They have played a special
role in pushing forward the motherland's economic development,
supporting the disaster relief work and promoting the
reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Qian pointed out that the situation after the return of Hong
Kong has proved the success of the implementation of the principle
of "one country, two systems". Cross straits exchanges have
increased in recent years, which indicates a general trend towards
the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
He added that the principles of "peaceful reunification" and "
one country, two systems" are also feasible in resolving the
Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed the hope that the overseas Chinese in Hong Kong
will make efforts to further expand cross straits exchanges.
</P>
<P>
He also exchanged opinions on foreign affairs and issues
concerning overseas Chinese with members of the delegation, and
answered their questions.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Overseas Chinese General Association, founded in
December 1993, is an influential patriotic social organization in
the region, with more than 800 members and five member
organizations. 
</P>
