<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus' acting president and
parliament speaker Spyros Kyprianou announced here Wednesday he is
mediating for the release of three United States soldiers captured
in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
According to the Cyprus News Agency (CNA), Kyprianou is flying
to Belgrade Wednesday afternoon via Athens, Greece to meet
Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic over the issue.
</P>
<P>
