<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue Rising in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices continued rising in
Tokyo Wednesday, with the key Nikkei index closing above 16,500
for the first time in eight and a half months.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 74.79 points, or 0.45
percent, from Tuesday's close to end at 16,554.50.
</P>
<P>
The last time the key index closed above 16,500 was July 21
last year, when it ended at 16,556.69.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, gained 2.03 points, or 0.15 percent, to 1,
324.64.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 709.61 million
shares from Tuesday's 568.21 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Akai Electronic was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors, who have returned to the market after the
Easter holiday, have actively resumed buying stocks in Tokyo,
driving share prices higher, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outnumbered
losers 762 to 466, with 98 issues remaining unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
