<HEADLINE> BT, SmarTone Announce Strategic Alliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 7 (Xinhua) -- British Telecommunications (BT)
announced Wednesday that it is forming an alliance with Hong
Kong's SmarTone telecommunication Holdings Limited (SmarTone)
through a direct equity purchase of 20 percent of the enlarged
share capital on a fully diluted basis.
</P>
<P>
This was made possible through the issuance of 120,782,250 new
shares in SmarTone, a leading provider of digital mobile
communication services in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The move by BT, one of the largest telecommunication companies
in the world, represents a 3 billion-HK dollar (384.6 million U.S.
dollars) investment in SmarTone at a price of 25 HK dollars (3.2 U.
S. dollars) per share. The strategic alliance will make BT
SmarTone's second largest shareholder.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the alliance at a press conference at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center, Hubert Ng, chief executive
officer of SmarTone, said that BT's commitment to SmarTone
demonstrates its confidence in the group's prospects, and equally
important, the future outlook of the telecommunications industry
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Also at the press conference, Richard Slogrove, managing
director of BT Asia Pacific, said that SmarTone's experience,
operational capabilities and managerial assets are not only well
suited to the growth of the Hong Kong market, but may also assist
BT in expanding into the China market as well as opportunities
arise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
