<HEADLINE> Canadian Gunman Kills Four in Ottawa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A former Ottawa City bus driver who
was reportedly angry over his treatment at the hands of his co-
workers opened fire on them Tuesday at the city's central bus
garage, killing four and wounding two before turning the gun on
himself.
</P>
<P>
The National Capital's first mass murder began about 2:39 p.m.
when the gunman, identified by co-workers as Pierre LeBrun, who
reportedly quit his job as bus company clerk earlier this year,
drove his car into the company's sprawling maintenance garage.
</P>
<P>
He pulled out a high-powered calibre hunting rifle and cut a
deadly path through the building, apparently firing at anything
and anyone that moved as bus mechanics and others raced for cover.
</P>
<P>
By 6 p.m., police had found the body of LeBrun, believed to
have been in his 40s, near one of the bus garage's maintenance
bays. Policy have not released the contents of the gunman's
suicide note.
</P>
<P>
The city will begin to mark the tragedy Wednesday by lowering
its flags. 
</P>
</TEXT>
