<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 3,000 soldiers and local
people in north China's Shanxi Province are still fighting a
forest fire in Wenshui County as they have put the blaze under
control in neighboring Fenyang County, sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The provincial forest fire prevention headquarters also
reported recovery of the bodies of the 23 inadequately-equipped
villagers who died fighting the fire that broke out on April 3 in
the juncture of the two counties.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 firemen are also participating in the effort,
which is being directed by provincial Vice-Governor Fan Duixiang.
</P>
<P>
State Council leaders have asked to spare no effort to
extinguish the fire, while officials and experts from the State
Forestry Bureau have rushed to the site.
</P>
<P>
According to the headquarters, people are still looking for
better ways to deal with the fire in Wenshui.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the forest fire has been unknown.  
