<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Telecom to be Reorganized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Minister of Information Industry Wu Jichuan has announced
that China Telecom will be divided into a fixed telephone, mobile
telecommunications, paging services and satellite
telecommunications companies.
</P>
<P>
With assets estimated at 560 billion yuan, China Telecom
currently accounts for about 95 percent of the telecoms service
market.
</P>
<P>
"The breaking up of China Telecom is aimed at smashing the
telecommunications monopoly in China and introducing competition
to set up a fair and orderly market," Wu said
</P>
<P>
So far, the only other operator authorized to offer nationwide
telecommunications services is China Unicom, which has assets of
only 130 million yuan and accounts for five percent of the market.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that his ministry is busy drafting the Law of
Telecommunications, and before the law is adopted, the ministry
will first promulgate Telecommunications Regulations in the first
half of this year to regulate the market.
</P>
<P>
China will further enhance exchanges with other countries in
telecommunications sector and introduce overseas capital in an
active and steady manner, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
