<DOCNO> XIE19990407.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Strengthens Supervision Of Construction Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua)-- China is strengthening supervision
of infrastructure-construction project management in the wake of
serious illegal fund appropriation and mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance issued a circular recently urging all
local governments and concerned departments to take direct
responsibility to ensure the sound management of construction
projects.
</P>
<P>
The circular pointed out several problems related to
construction projects that must not be neglected, noting that some
projects were improperly planned while others were begun with
insufficient funding.
</P>
<P>
In some cases, construction project budgets were frequently
changed, causing a dilution of funds and huge waste, it said.
</P>
<P>
The circular was released after a much-publicized project
involving the collapse of a bridge in Chongqing City in southwest
China. On January 4, the bridge collapsed in Qijiang County,
killing 40 people and injuring 14 others, and resulting in direct
economic loss of over six million yuan. The bridge was built amid
serious bribery, dereliction of duty, and mismanagement, and the
case ended with the death sentence on a leading county official
and 13 others sentenced to prison terms of three to 13 years.
</P>
<P>
The circular stresses that local government and department
leaders take particular care of infrastructure construction
projects, from approval to completion.
</P>
<P>
The circular also demands that builders appear in the role of
legal persons and registered companies, so that direct
responsibility for financial and accounting management can be
pinpointed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
