<HEADLINE> Giant Panda Killers Sentenced in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A local court in southwest China's
Sichuan Province Tuesday sentenced five farmers for killing a
giant panda and selling its skin.
</P>
<P>
They will serve one to five years in prison and pay fines of 1,
000 to 2,000 yuan, according to the ruling of the People's Court
of Qingyang District in the city of Chengdu, the provincial
capital.
</P>
<P>
In April 1997, Yuan Rugang and Yang Tianbin killed a giant
panda in Qingchuan County. Yuan later sold the skin to Tian
Zhongmu and Jiu Shengqiang, from Jiangyou County. Tian and Jiu
then had their friend Wang Xiuguang take the skin to Chengdu where
Wang was caught red-handed by local police.
</P>
<P>
Over 60 giant pandas live in the Tangjiahe Giant Panda Nature
Reserve in Qingchuan County.
</P>
<P>
Giant pandas are found only in China, where there are only
about 1,000 of the endangered animals left in the wild. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
