<HEADLINE> 6 Killed in Turkish Airlines Jet Crash in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- All six crew members were killed
early Wednesday when a Turkish Airlines passenger plane crashed in
southern Turkey, the Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said the Boeing 737-400 plane named "Trakya" was
engulfed in fire soon after taking off from Adana Airport and
crashed near the Ceyhan town, 40 kilometers east of Adana,
southern Turkey. No passengers were on board.
</P>
<P>
The plane was en route to Jeddah, Saudi Arabia to bring back
Turkish pilgrims after their visits to Muslim holy cities.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Transport Minister Hasan Basri Aktan said it was rainy
and windy in Adana when the plane crashed, adding the cause
of the crash has not been established.
</P>
<P>
A team of bomb experts was sent to the site of the crash to
investigate into the incident, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
It added that the "black box" has been found under a
seven-meter-depth hole in the crash area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
