<HEADLINE> Three Natural Resource Study Centers to Be Built in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences (
CAS) will build three natural resource research centers in Beijing,
northwest and southwest China to meet the country's economic
development and environmental protection needs.
</P>
<P>
A resource and environment center, on a par with the most
advanced level in east Asia, will be built in Beijing, under the
guidance of the Institute of Geophysics and the Institute of
Geology, said Chen Yiyu, vice-president of the CAS.
</P>
<P>
The two institutes will co-operate with the institutes of
Remote Sensing Application and Atmospheric Physics and the
Ecological Environment Research Center to form a national network.
</P>
<P>
Another center will be built in northwest China, said Chen. The
projects will be on a very large scale, from Xi'an City to Gansu
Province and Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region. It will cover the
Northwest Institute of Soil and Water Conservation, the Lanzhou
Institute of Desert, the Lanzhou Institute of Glaciology and
Cryopedology, the Lanzhou Institute of Plateau Atmospheric Physics,
the Lanzhou Institute of Geology and Institute of Northwest
Plateau Biology.
</P>
<P>
He explained that the third research center, which will target
the development of biological resources and the protection of
biodiversity, will be built in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
He added that during the first phase of the construction of the
centers, the CAS will also be involved in some major research
projects, to meet the needs of national economic construction.
</P>
</TEXT>
