<HEADLINE> China's Tree Growing Campaign A Huge Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua)-- China has planted 33.79 million ha
of trees over the past 20 years, a world record, the State
Forestry Administration has claimed.
</P>
<P>
It revealed that China's forestry coverage rate was raised to
13.92 percent from 12.7 percent at the start of the 1980s, the
biggest project being the planting of a belt of trees along the
north of the "Great Wall".
</P>
<P>
An administration report also revealed that 12 provinces and
autonomous regions have afforested a considerable number of
formerly barren mountains.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 20 years, there have been nearly five billion
participants in the tree planting drive, resulting in two billion
new trees a year, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The national tree planting campaign started in 1979, when the
National People's Congress Standing Committee set March 12 as the
national tree planting day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
