<HEADLINE> Nigeria's New Salary System Offers $3,900 to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has released a new salary
structure and allowances for top federal public office holders of
the in-coming government of Nigeria, according to a New Nigerian
report Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the new package, outlined by the National Salaries,
Incomes and Wages Commission, the president of Nigeria is to earn
350,000 naira (about 3,900 U.S. dollars) per annum as against
87,000 naira previously earned by occupants of the office.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president and chief Justice of Nigeria are placed at
par on an annual salary of 286,800 naira (3,187 Dollars) as
against 77,400 naira earned by the holders of the office.
</P>
<P>
The senate president is to earn 261,000 naira (2,900 Dollars)
as against the previous annual salary of 70,500 naira while
speaker of the House of Representative, Justices of the Supreme
Court and president of the Court of Appeal are placed on annual
salaries 236,400 naira (about 2,627 Dollars) as against 63,900
naira previously paid them.
</P>
<P>
Secretary to the Federal Government, ministers, chairmen of the
Civil Service Commission, Federal Character Commission, Deputy
president of the Senate, Justices of Court of Appeal, Chief Judge
of Federal High Court are placed on the same grade of 216,000
naira (about 2,400 Dollars) as against their former salaries of
58,200 naira per annum.
</P>
<P>
In the 1999 budget broadcast to the nation, Nigerian Head of
State General Abdulsalam Abubakar said in January the Nigerian
government has abolished the official exchange rate of its
currency naira fixed at 22 to the U.S. Dollar and announced an
exchange rate of 86 naira to the Dollar, and the naira devalued
last month to 90 to the dollar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
