<HEADLINE> Beijing Acrobatics School Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Acrobatics School, the
first of its kind in this capital city, was recently established
at the training center for the China Acrobatics Troupe.
</P>
<P>
Though China is well-known for its acrobatics, the country
previously had no school for professional training, and the common
practice was to employ experienced acrobats to teach apprentices
or to train novice acrobats at local art schools.
</P>
<P>
The newly built school covers an area of 38,000 square meters
and has advanced teaching facility. It is authorized to enroll 200
students from both domestic and overseas primary and middle
schools.
</P>
<P>
The school will offer specialties including acrobatics, magic,
and circus performances, and students will receive seven years of
systematic training along with general knowledge courses.
</P>
<P>
Lin Jian, head of the China Acrobatics Troupe, is acting as the
president of the school which already has enrolled its first 100
students, 20 of whom are from Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
