<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Marginally Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
marginally lower Wednesday after trading in a tight range on the
session.
</P>
<P>
After suffering offshore selling Tuesday night the Australian
dollar recovered to open only slightly below the previous close.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslavian announcement of a ceasefire put paid to the
European and U.S. selling of the Australian currency, which closed
in Sydney Wednesday at 63.06 U.S. cents, from 63.09 U.S. cents
Tuesday.
</P>
