<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Holds Talks with Syrian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, the Chinese top legislator,
held talks with his Syrian counterpart Abdel Kader Kaddura here
Tuesday evening to exchange views on bilateral and international
issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC) of China, arrived here late Tuesday
afternoon on a three-day official visit,
</P>
<P>
Li said it is good for promoting friendship and cooperation
between China and Syria that leaders of the two countries keep
regular contacts to exchange views and opinions on bilateral ties
and regional and international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
China cherishes its traditional friendship and cooperation with
Syria, he said, adding that to further strengthen the bilateral
ties is not only in the fundamental interest of the two peoples,
but also conducive to enhancing the unity and cooperation among
developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Li also said the NPC would like to step up its cooperation
and expand exchanges with the People's Council of Syria in order to
promote the mutual understanding between the peoples of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Kaddura, president of the People's Council, said Syria and
China have always been enjoying a friendly relationship since the
diplomatic ties was established between the two countries in the
1950s, despite whatever happened in the world.
</P>
<P>
The current visit by Li Peng to Syria is an important event in
the development of the bilateral relations, he said, adding
Syria attaches extreme importance to developing cooperation with
China.
</P>
<P>
Syria is grateful to the help China offered to Syria in the
areas of politics, economy, and culture. And Syria is willing to
further develop the friendly cooperation between the two
countries, the two parliaments and the two peoples, Kaddura said.
</P>
