<HEADLINE> Applied Intelligent Computer Systems Used for Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Applied Intelligent Computer
Systems have been used to train 95 percent of China's strategic
missile force.
</P>
<P>
Liberation Army Daily reported that the Second Artillery Force
have shortened the period of new equipment's formation of
combating forces.
</P>
<P>
Training on applied intelligent computer systems has raised the
successful launch rate for missiles to 100 percent.
</P>
<P>
The nation's major military ranges have installed computerized
systems which quickly and accurately eliminate all obstacles
involving missile launches.
</P>
<P>
The Second Artillery Force has established a number of
computerized missile training ranges and developed software and
hundreds computer-aided design (CAD) training programs in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
The force has also developed over 1,000 simulated training
devices and new military equipment items.
</P>
<P>
High-tech systems which have replaced obsolete training devices
and installations have guaranteed safe and effective training for
the strategic missile force. 
