<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Using Overseas Funds for Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Agricultural production in Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region in northwest China had enjoyed sustainable
and fast growth thanks to the use of overseas funds over the past
16 years.
</P>
<P>
By early this year, Xinjiang had used 49.48 million U.S.
dollars in overseas loans to help develop agriculture in addition
to overseas grants of 8.14 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang began using overseas funds to develop agriculture in
1983.
</P>
<P>
Now six farming technology spreading centers and seed stations
have been set up with the implementation of the first phase of the
World Bank-financed agricultural irrigation project in the Tarim
basin over the past three years.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of the project which involves 150 million
dollars is under way. Water control facilities, agricultural and
environmental projects will be built in 22 counties and cities in
southern Xinjiang.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, the European Union (EU) has given free aid to
Xinjiang totaling 4.5 million dollars to help raise agricultural
output. The EU has also offered technical know-how, instrument and
training services for Chinese technicians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
