<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Government Forces Suspend Strikes Against KLA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav government forces have
suspended all military operations against the outlawed Kosovo
Liberation Arm (KLA) in the southern province of the Serbian
republic.
</P>
<P>
The unilateral cease-fire, as reported by the Tanjug news
agency quoting a press release from the local military
headquarters in Pristina, was in line with a decision made by the
Yugoslav and Serbian governments.
</P>
<P>
The authorities issued a communique Tuesday to effect a cease-
fire from 20:00 local time as an effort to facilitate a political
solution to the Kosovo crisis and the return of ethnic Albanian
refugees to their homes.
</P>
<P>
Except NATO bombings, said the news release of the local
military headquarters, situation is rather peaceful in Kosovo, and
local residents and United Nations and international Red Cross
workers are free to move. 
