<DOCNO> XIE19990407.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Armed Forces Pledges to Prevent Clash in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Commander of the Indonesian
National Armed Forces (TNI), Gen. Wiranto, has ordered security
personnel to prevent East Timor from inter-group clashing.
</P>
<P>
TNI and the Police Department will take strict measures to
restore law enforcement as well as human rights and public order
in East Timor, Wiranto said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Pro-independence groups of the Timorese Struggle Council (CNRT)
and its military wing Timor Leste National Armed Forces
(Falintil), led by jailed Alexander Xanana Gusmao, has declared
war against the Indonesian government and TNI, who have allegedly
been arming pro-integrationist group.
</P>
<P>
Xanana on Monday abruptly abandoned his ceasefire and told East
Timorese to take up arms against Indonesian rule following a clash
in East Timor Liquica district over the weekend during which 17
pro-independence supporters were reportedly killed and two
pro-integrationist East Timorese were stabbed to death.
</P>
<P>
Twelve houses were damaged and burned in the clashes in
Liquica, about 38 kilometers west of East Timor's capital of Dili,
reports said.
</P>
<P>
Xanana said he will revoke his call to arms only if the United
Nations send its peace-keeping forces to disarm the militia in
East Timor.
</P>
<P>
East Timor, with a population of some 800,000 and an area of
15,000 square kilometers, had been a Portuguese colony until 1975,
it became an Indonesian province in 1976, but the U.N. never
recognized the move.
</P>
<P>
On January 27, the Indonesian government announced that it is
ready to release East Timor if the alternative to provide wider
autonomy is refused by people in the region and the international
community.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian government has suggested that the U.N.-sponsored
direct balloting to determine if the East Timor wants autonomy or
independence should be held in July this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
