<DOCNO> XIE19990407.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 06:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> GCC countries to Hold Trade Fair in Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The six Gulf Cooperation Council
(GCC) countries are making preparations for a joint trade fair in
Kazakhstan next month, the Khaleej Times daily reported on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time ever such a fair is being held outside
the Gulf. All the past 11 exhibitions were hosted by the member
countries in rotation, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Private sectors in Oman, the UAE, Qatar, Bahrain, Saudi Arabia
and Kuwait are being urged to participate in large numbers at the
12th GCC Joint Exhibition to be held from May 11 to 15.
</P>
<P>
"The event will provide companies in the Gulf a big opportunity
to explore new markets for their products," Sheikh Salim,
President of the Oman Chamber of Commerce and Industry (OCCI), was
quoted by the paper as saying in Muscat.
</P>
<P>
More than 10 companies in Oman have confirmed their
participation in the fair, and the number is expected to rise
significantly in the coming weeks, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the exhibition would give a boost to trade relations
between the GCC and Kazakhstan as well as providing an opportunity
for Gulf businessmen to know more about that country.
</P>
<P>
The fair is being organized by the GCC secretary general in
collaboration with the Union of GCC Chambers of Commerce and
Industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
