<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed lower here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 30 points lower at 2,105 with a turnover
of 69 million N.Z. dollars (36.8 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Almost all leading stocks dropped except for Fletcher Building
which edged up 1 cent to 247 cents.
</P>
<P>
AMP was the biggest loser, falling 50 cents to 2,050 cents,
followed by Fletcher Energy down 15 to 345 cents, Sky City down 13
to 755 cents, and Telecom down 12 to 895 cents.
</P>
<P>
Carter Holt Harvey lost 7 cents to 174 cents and Air New
Zealand-A 5 to 275 cents. Both Lion Nathan and Fletcher Paper
dropped 3 cents to 455 and 113 cents respectively, while Brierley
Investments shed 2 to 45 cents. 
</P>
