<HEADLINE> Senior Official: Amended Copyright Law to Be Adopted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislature is
deliberating the amended copyright law which is scheduled to be
adopted in August, Shen Rengan, deputy administrator of the
Copyright Administration said in today's Guangming Daily.
</P>
<P>
Experts on copyright protection is revising the law to adapt
itself to the new circumstances of the ongoing market economy, the
Beijing-based newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The administration Tuesday organized a high-profile symposium
on protecting copyright in the country, it said.
</P>
<P>
Shen said that the administration will further cooperate with
legal authorities.
</P>
<P>
Symposium participants from north China's Beijing and Tianjin
municipalities, and Hebei Province and northwestern Shaanxi
Province studied new cases of copyright infringement. 
</P>
