<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Trade Information Publisher Opens Chinese Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua)-- Asian Sources, Asia's largest
independent trade information publisher, opened a Chinese language
website in Beijing yesterday.
</P>
<P>
At the website, surfers will find more than 200 up-to-date
articles on management and MBA courses offered at Chinese and
foreign universities.
</P>
<P>
The website is also connected to well-known international
management consulting companies and international management
seminars. Economists will also be invited to discuss enterprise
problems on the site.
</P>
<P>
Asian Sources publishes information for buyers and suppliers
worldwide and also provides software for trade information.
</P>
<P>
Brandon Smith, general manager of Asian Sources' China Regional
Operations, said that the website was created because the Chinese
economy has been expanding rapidly and has become a major
component of the global economy.
</P>
<P>
Asian Sources entered China in the early years of the country's
reform and opening-up drive initiated in 1979, and now has 30
subsidiary organizations in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
