<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Securities Market Helping Ningxia's Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The economic development of
northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region has got a great
deal of help from the rapid growth of its securities business,
according to Li Jinyu, an official of Regional Securities
Regulatory Commission.
</P>
<P>
Li, director of the commission's general office, used the
first company to be listed, the Guangxia Share-Holding Co. Ltd.,
as an example by pointing to its assets, which increased from 90
million yuan in 1994 to 1.48 billion yuan last year. The State-
owed enterprise built a 1,300-ha Chinese medicinal herb production
area on desert land by using local resources.
</P>
<P>
The company has also built a 1,300-ha. grape growing area on
the eastern slope of the Helan Mountains to produce wine in
cooperation with a French company.
</P>
<P>
The region has put medicine and wine on its list of pillar
industries to promote local economic development. Preferential
policies for listed companies for funds and taxes have helped
these enterprises give the region new growth.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia now has 7 companies in electronics, machine-building,
chemicals, metals, trade, paper-making, and instruments that have
been listed and 5 securities companies, with 96,000 shareholders,
compared with a few hundred just 5 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The listed companies raised 1.5 billion yuan in total by
issuing shares. By the end of last June, the turnover of their
stocks had hit 11.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Incomes of the 7 listed companies were up 54 percent, profits
were up 77 percent, and assets increased 57 percent in value from
the same period in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
