<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia-Pacific Air Passenger Market Posts Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The air passenger market recorded
another month of moderate growth for the Association of
Asia-Pacific Airlines (AAPA) members in November 1998, the
Philippines News Agency said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
AAPA was quoted as saying that it was the third consecutive
month that air passenger traffic had increased and reflected an
improving business climate.
</P>
<P>
Revenue passenger kilometers grew 3.0 percent and passengers
carried rose 2.3 percent during the period, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Excluding the results of the financially-troubled Philippine
Airlines, the consolidated AAPA results for November showed a more
robust traffic growth of 6.1 percent and a 5.1 percent rise in
passengers carried, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
With a few exceptions, the effects of the Asian financial
crisis appear to have bottomed out for most of the AAPA members,
it said.
</P>
<P>
As a summary, improved passenger traffic for three successive
months appears to support the observation that the travel industry
in the region is on the mend, the agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
