<HEADLINE> Chinese Antiques Going On Display In Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Museum of Chinese History
plans to put some antiques that have never been exhibited before
on display.
</P>
<P>
The museum plans to put 2,000 items on display for a restricted
number of visitors daily.
</P>
<P>
The museum is one of China's most-renowned sites of historic
treasures, but only 5,000 items are on display at any time because
of the limited number of exhibition halls and poor lighting and
temperature controls.
</P>
<P>
Another 300,000 rare antiques, mainly paintings, calligraphic
works, and silk fabrics have been kept in storehouses with better
lighting and humidity controls.
</P>
<P>
The museum is expected to add a "treasure hall" in a few months.
