<P>
Signatories were Director of the Chinese National Tourism
Administration He Guangwei and Director of the Vietnam Tourism
Administration Vo Thi Thang.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the two sides will send a
five-member delegation each year for tourism development research
and exchange of information and statistics on tourism development
of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation in tourism development, hotel management and
personnel training is another aim of the agreement. China and
Vietnam will also boost cooperation in advertisement to attract
more visitors from third countries and to encourage tourism
agencies to take part in fairs, seminars and other events relating
to tourism.
</P>
<P>
Tourism heads of the two countries, at their talks on Tuesday,
exchanged information on tourism activities in their respective
countries and reviewed cooperation between the two tourism
administrations in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Chinese visitors to Vietnam increased from 17,000 in 1993 to
400,000 in 1997 and 420,000 last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics of Vietnamese department concerned,
China has seven projects investing in Vietnam's tourism industry
at a combined capital of 28.5 million U.S. dollars, and Hong Kong
has 28 projects worth 424.4 million U.S. dollars, accounting for 4
percent of foreign invested capital in the field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
