<HEADLINE> Peru's Fishing Industry Recovering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Peru's fish production at the end of
the first quarter of this year rose to 373,000 metric tons, or 446.
1 percent over the same period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Peru's National Fishing Society (NFS) President Jose Sarmiento
said Tuesday that the growth rate reflected the recovery of the
sector, which was seriously affected last year by the negative
effects of the "El Nino" weather phenomenon characterized by a
massive warming of the surface waters of the tropical eastern
Pacific Ocean.
</P>
<P>
The NFS estimated that the output of fish oil at the end of the
first quarter was 73,500 metric tons, up 1,570 percent from the
corresponding period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Fish exports in the first quarter reached 162.2 million U.S.
dollars, up 35 percent from a year earlier, said the official.
</P>
