<HEADLINE> Yunnan Invests Heavily To Help Poor Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The programs has helped poor farmers have enough food and
clothing.
</P>
<P>
Under the programs, each of the poor rural households are
allocated enough farmland to grow grain and cash crops, and
meanwhile, communications, telecommunications and farming
infrastructure will be much improved.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, 95 percent of local villages have telephone services
and access to road networks. Substantial measures have been taken
to resolve the shortage of drinking water and the electricity
supply in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
As the first province to introduce the Bangladeshi model of
granting small loans to poor farmers, Yunnan has adopted the
scheme across 90 percent of its countryside, with loans totaling
350 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, a government resettlement program is being
implemented for rural people in remote or mountain areas whose
living conditions are too poor to be improved. So far, over 40,000
of them have been relocated.  
