<HEADLINE> Short Persons Association Walks Tall in Jilin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- In a bid to help short students
get rid of any inferiority complexes and take part in campus
activities, physical education teacher Chi Hua, himself a short
person, has set up a special association to tackle the problem
</P>
<P>
"We should always keep in mind that we are equal with others no
matter what size we may," said 43 year old Chi, who is chairman
of the "Short Persons Association" in the Changchun University of
Science and Technology, in northeast China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
Tao Xiaohong, the college's shortest student, said that the
association has helped build up her confidence and to face any
problems with ease.
</P>
<P>
"The society has been very popular among short college students
ever since its establishment last December and I am really glad to
see that the club has helped its members get rid of an unnecessary
psychological burden," said Chi.
</P>
<P>
The members often play basketball with other college teams and
although they often lose, their performances often win them
applause and respect. "They are really great," a number of their
opponents commented.
</P>
<P>
"Most people in the south or China are short compared with
northerners. As a result we are not able to join in a lot of
competitive sports. We feel very depressed at this," added Chi.
</P>
<P>
"However, the association has provided us with opportunities
to show our potential," said Zhao Suoping, who is a short
southerner from Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
Height is the only requirement for membership. Anyone shorter
than 166 centimeters can apply and so far there are more than 100
members, with an average height of 163 centimeters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
