<HEADLINE> Brazil's Car Sales Doubled in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANIERO, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Car sales in Brazil reached
70,000 units in March, a rate which is almost double that of
February last year (36,000), said a source representing Car Sales
Association in Brazil on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It was said that the sales increase was due to discount prices
within the sector, and also due to the stability of the local
currency,real, against the dollar.
</P>
<P>
"Consumers always take advantage of discounts, the time is
right for people with money" said Mario Braga, director of the
association.
</P>
<P>
However, the National Association of Car Manufacturers forecast
that total car sales in 1999 would fall by ten percent in
comparison with last year.
</P>
<P>
"Certainly 1999 will be more difficult than last year, but it
is supposed that businesses may recuperate in the second half of
the year" said Braga.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the total car production in Brazil was 1.6 million
units, a 20 prcent drop in comparison with more than 2 million in
1997. 
</P>
