<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian Witnessing Lowest Birth Rate in Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Southeast China's Fujian Province
brought down the natural population growth rate to 5.3 per 1,000
last year, touching the lowest point in 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Fujian had witnessed one of the fastest population growths
among China's provinces with its population increasing to 32
million from eleven million in 40 years.
</P>
<P>
However, the growth momentum has slowed down as the "One Child"
family planning policy has been more effectively carried out in
recent years. Fujian recorded 379,500 new births last year with a
net annual population growth of 170,000 people, which represents
the province's lowest record, since the founding of the New China
in 1949. 
</P>
</TEXT>
