<HEADLINE> World Health Day Dedicated to Pensioners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The Pan-American Health
Organization (PAHO) will celebrate "World Health Day" on Wednesday,
which will be dedicated to retired people. PAHO has adopted the
slogan "We stay active to grow old well," the PAHO secretariat
said in a statement on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The group's statement claimed that it is important to establish
national systems of healthcare in order to provide better
healthcare and attention to the aged.
</P>
<P>
In the year 2025, it said the population of people over the age
of 60 living in Latin America and the Caribbean will rise from 42
million to 97 million, while in the U.S. and Canada there will be
98 million.
</P>
<P>
The secretariat said the PAHO will conduct studies to learn
about health conditions among the older generation in seven urban
centers of Latin America and the Caribbean: Barbados, Brazil,
Chile, Costa Rica, Mexico, Cuba and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
"The compiled information will help to familiarize us with the
chronic and acute diseases of the elderly," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It also said the information would contribute to the formation
of future health programs, and provide an acceptable model of well-
being for the elderly. 
</P>
