<HEADLINE> Venezuela Oil Prices Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Oil prices in Venezuela rose 8.7
percent Monday from last week due to cuts in production, an Energy
and Mines Ministry official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Alvaro Silva Caldero, general director of the ministry, said
the rise of oil prices should be attributed to the production
reduction agreement reached between the Organization of the
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) and independent producers
last month.
</P>
<P>
Oil prices rose from 12.32 dollars a barrel last week to 13.40
Monday.
</P>
<P>
