<HEADLINE> Sri Lank's Ruling PA Wins North Central Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lank's Ruling People's
Alliance (PA) won North Central Provincial Council in Tuesday's
five provincial council elections, the Elections Commissioner
announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first province won by the PA in the crucial
elections ahead of parliamentary and presidential elections due
next year.
</P>
<P>
The PA won 53.39 percent votes or 19 out of 33 seats, beating
the main opposition United National Party, which got 39.46 percent
votes or 12 seats, and the People's Liberation Front which got
5.23 percent votes or 2 seats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
