<HEADLINE> Fowler Fined by Liverpool </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 6 (Xinhua) -- England striker Robbie Fowler was
fined and given a formal warning by his Liverpool club on Tuesday
over his controversial "cocaine" goal celebrations in Saturday's
match against Everton.
</P>
<P>
After scoring a 15th minute penalty, Fowler twice knelt down
and sniffed the white goal-line in a simulated display of drug-
taking in response to chants by Everton supporters about an
alleged drug habit.
</P>
<P>
Foster, already facing an English F.A hearing on Friday over a
misconduct charge following a clash with Chelsea defender and
England teammate Graeme Le Saux in February, was further charged
by the F.A on Tuesday over the Anfield incident.
</P>
<P>
He was ordered to appear before a Liverpool board meeting and
told of his fine, believed to be two weeks' wages.
</P>
<P>
Liverpool chairman David Moores said: "The club deeply regret
what happened on the field and made it very clear that they would
not allow any player or other persons to damage the club's
reputation without taking a firm response.
</P>
<P>
"The club, however, recognise that for far too long Robbie has
been the subject of totally unjustified allegations and rumours
about drugs and other personal matters which can only be described
as a pack of lies.
</P>
<P>
"There was also the long period during which he feared that his
career might be over as the result of an extremely serious injury.
</P>
<P>
"The club now regard the matter as closed and have accepted the
player's assurances that he will not give any further grounds for
complaint."
</P>
<P>
Fowler publicly apologised for his behaviour on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He issued a statement saying: "I would like to apologise
unequivocally for my first goal celebration.
</P>
<P>
"Despite my actions being taken in the heat of the moment I
realise that they have caused great offence."
</P>
<P>
Fowler got into trouble in the league match with Chelsea when
he bent over and pointed to his backside in an attempt to cast a
'gay' slur on the heterosexual Le Saux.
</P>
<P>
Le Saux was also charged with misconduct after video pictures
showed the Chelsea player elbowing Fowler in the face. 
</P>
</TEXT>
