<HEADLINE> PFA Suggest New Fine Scheme </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The Professional Footballers
Association (PFA) proposed on Tuesday a new scheme of fines for
players for disciplinary offences from next season.
</P>
<P>
Players could lose some of their wages for picking up eight
bookings and there may be stiffer penalties for red cards.
</P>
<P>
However, PFA chief executive Gordon Taylor stressed the maximum
penalty would be two weeks' salary.
</P>
<P>
"We are trying to be even-handed," he said. "Players have
commitments which is why the measures would only come in after
eight games." 
</P>
</TEXT>
