<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Moves Lower On Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
moved lower Tuesday as Gillettee warned that its first quarter
profits will probably not meet investors' expectations.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed at 9,963.49, down 43.84 from the record closing
high of 10,007.33, set Monday.
</P>
<P>
Gillettee's announcement discouraged investors who bid stocks
higher Monday on expectations of strong corporate profits in the
first quarter.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mixed. The technology heavy
Nasdaq composite index rose 3.11 at 2,563.17 while the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index was down 3.23 at 1,317.89.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index was down 2.31 at 612.32 and the American Stock
Exchange index was down 6.03 at 715.21. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies fell 1.21 at 401.08.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 3-to-2 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,789 down, 1,193 up and 594
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 785.88 million shares from 694.42
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
